Package SalamiRuntime

Class Interpreter

java.lang.Object
SalamiRuntime.Interpreter
public class Interpreter extends Object

Handles interpreting of an AST structure. Pass in any StatementNode to the evaluate(StatementNode) method to begin interpreting.

    • evaluate

      public static Value evaluate(StatementNode s, Environment environment, ProgramCounter pc, ProgramNode program) throws InterpreterException, ValueException

      Evaluates a single statement. A

      Parameters:
      s - The statement to be evaluated.
      environment - The environment which should be modified.
      pc - The program counter so we know where we are in the program.
      Returns:
      the correctly evaluated statement.
      Throws:
      InterpreterException - If it encounters a statement which it doesn't have an evaluator function for, it throws an error.
      ValueException - If at any point two values are mismatched, or some other error like that, this gets thrown.

    • evaluate_print_statement

      public static VoidValue evaluate_print_statement(PrintStatement printNode, Environment env, ProgramCounter pc, ProgramNode program) throws InterpreterException
      Evaluates print statements like:
      print 'Hello, world!
      Parameters:
      printNode - The PrintStatement AST node to be evaluated.
      env - The environment to grab identifiers from.
      pc - The program counter. Does not have to be a specific counter, as it will never be used.
      Returns:
      a VoidValue.
      Throws:
      InterpreterException - In case the evaluation of what needs to be printed goes wrong.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      a VoidValue.
      Throws:
      InterpreterException - If what we are defining the variable as can't be evaluated, then it throws an error.

    • evaluate_program

      public static Value evaluate_program(ProgramNode p, Environment environment, ProgramCounter startingpc, boolean initializeProgram) throws InterpreterException, ValueException

      Takes in a ProgramNode and evaluates each StatementNode in the program. Pass in an Environment and a ProgramCounter so it can properly modify variables and use jump statements.

      Parameters:
      p - The program node which needs to be evaluated.
      environment - The environment which can be changed as the program gets evaluated.
      startingpc - The starting program counter, in case we wanted to start from a different program counter for any reason.
      initializeProgram - Controls whether the program should be initialized or not. This will be off for subroutines because they are already initialized in the first loop.
      Returns:
      the evaluation of the last statement.
      Throws:
      InterpreterException - If a statement fails to be evaluated, an InterpreterException will occur.
      ValueException
      See Also:
      • Initializer
